ven in the Gulf countries. According to The Economist "in the past year (2002) overall business at western fast-food and drinks firms has dropped by 40% in Arab countries. Trade in American branded goods has shrunk by a quarter."
\par These are bad news. Multinationals are sizable employers. Coca-Cola alone is responsible for 220,000 jobs in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns1{\factoidname place}}Middle East{\*\xmlclose}. Procter & Gamble invested $100 million in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns1{\factoidname 
